[ProMED-mail thanks Dr Nowotny and colleagues for this interesting
report. It will be interesting to see if results of the entire genome
sequencing of the apparently more virulent Greece WN virus compared
with the perhaps less virulent WN virus lineage 2 from Hungary and
Austria will lead to detection of the genetic basis for this
difference.

A map showing the location of Greek Central Macedonia, the site of
the WN virus outbreak, can be accessed at
<http://www.mlahanas.de/Greece/Regions/CentralMacedonia.html>.
A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map showing Greece, Hungary, and
Austria can be accessed at
<http://healthmap.org/r/07fx>. - Mod.TY]
